OL,3,CGovernment urged to review 'broken'
OL,4,Cdrug supply chain amid shortages
OL,6,FSome 1,634 alerts were issued in 2023,
OL,7,Fup from 648 in 2020. Researchers also
OL,8,Fpointed out that Britain has been
OL,9,Fslower to approve drugs than the EU.
OL,11,FBetween 2022 and 2023, four drugs
OL,12,Fauthorised by the European Commission
OL,13,F(EC) had been approved faster in
OL,14,FBritain. However, some 56 were
OL,15,Fapproved after the EC and eight have
OL,16,Fnot been approved at all as of March
OL,17,F2024.
