OL,3,CGovernment urged to review 'broken'
OL,4,Cdrug supply chain amid shortages
OL,6,FMr Dayan added: "The rise in shortages
OL,7,Fof vital medicines from rare to
OL,8,Fcommonplace has been a shocking
OL,9,Fdevelopment that few would have
OL,10,Fexpected a decade ago.
OL,12,F"More and more patients across the UK
OL,13,Fare experiencing a pharmacist telling
OL,14,Fthem that their medication is not
OL,15,Favailable, it may not be available
OL,16,Fsoon, and it may not be available
OL,17,Fanywhere nearby. This is also creating
OL,18,Fa great deal of extra work for both
OL,19,FGPs and pharmacists."
